==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pottle
<hw>Pot"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>potel</ets>,
OF. <ets>potel</ets>, dim. of <ets>pot</ets>. See <er>Pot</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A liquid measure of four pints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pot or tankard.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A dry <qex>pottle</qex> of sack before him.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A vessel or small basket for holding
fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had a . . . <qex>pottle</qex> of strawberries in one hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pottle draught</b></col>, <cd>taking a pottle of liquor
at one draught.</cd> <mark>[ Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Potto</ent>⟦br⟧
